==Scots==

===Etymology===
Vartiant of the Scots word ''[[lawlands]]'' meaning [[lowlands]] of [[Scotland]].

===Noun===
'''Lallans'''

# the [[Scots]] language, a Germanic language closely related to English and descended from northern dialects of Old English and using [[Gaelic]] loan words. It is spoken in parts of Scotland, in particular the south, central and [[Doric]] dialects. 
# [[Gaelic]] spoken with an [[English]] accent.

